LuguLake Turntables TN03 Editorial Review

The Lugulake Vintage Turntable is an excellent addition to any music lover's collection. This turntable has a vintage look and feel that will take you back to a time when vinyl was king. The sound quality is good, although not exceptional, with a tweeter speaker located in the horn and small speakers in the box. There is no CD player, but instead, the turntable boasts Bluetooth, AUX input port, USB port, FM and LP. Additionally, the cartridge, needle, and drive belt are replaceable, making it easy to maintain the longevity of the turntable. The only downside is that the horn is not as loud as some users might like it to be. Though, while the sound from the horn is not terrific, the sound from the speakers located around the box is excellent, and the tweeter speaker in the horn still adds a nice touch. Overall, the Lugulake Vintage Turntable is a great device for anyone who loves music, and the vintage design will look great in any home.
